Date: Monday, 15th April 2024

Name of the program: Avventura2 (Adventure2-escape from planet)
This program is a little italian text based 
adventure that I have written by Blitz2 (Blitz Basic 2.1).
This upload was made because I have cleaned the source code with a minimum of graphics improvement.
It is a bit more complex than my first one 
(StefADV.lha)
It can be played only by who knows italian language.
In the archive is supplied a font (Data70) that I have made for private use; to
play the adventure you must install it in your FONTS: drawer, proceeding as
follows: copy in your FONTS: drawer the file Data70.font; create a drawer named
Data70 in your FONTS: drawer, and copy into it the file 13.
I am not responsible of any damage this program can occurs to your system; you
use it at your own risk!
Note: I have used the TextLength_ function of the graphics.library for this
adventure; the sintax for this function, that I have learned from the blitz
mailing list in date 28th December 1999, is the following:

PixelTextLength.w=TextLength_(RastPort(Window),&Text$,Len(Text$))

